[3] Rabies - Pennsylvania
Date: 5 Aug 2016
Source: Patch.com [edited]
http://patch.com/pennsylvania/doylestown/groundhog-had-aggressive-encounters-doylestown-tests-positive-rabies


A groundhog captured in Doylestown after "a series of aggressive encounters" has tested positive for rabies, Doylestown Borough officials confirmed Friday [5 Aug 2016]. The groundhog, which had the aggressive encounters with both humans and pets, was captured in the vicinity of Church and Mechanic streets earlier this week, according to information from Doylestown Borough.

The Bucks County Department of Health notified Doylestown Borough officials of the positive test this week.

Authorities advise if you or your pets had an encounter with an aggressive groundhog, contact your family physician or veterinarian "immediately."

Further details on the aggressive encounters or how many were reported were not immediately available.

[Byline: Kara Symour]

