[4] Rabies - South Carolina
Date: 5 Aug 2016
Source: WYFF4.com [edited]
http://www.wyff4.com/news/upstate-dog-potentially-exposes-at-least-5-people-to-rabies-dhec-says/41072124


At least 5 people were potentially exposed to rabies by a puppy that tested positive for the disease in Chesnee, the Department of Health and Environmental Control [DHEC] reported today [5 Aug 2016].

The puppy was a Germany Shepherd-mix that was being sold at Burr's Trading Post on Old Stage Road on 20 Jun 2016 from an individual not affiliated with the store. The puppy began to show neurological symptoms at the end of July 2016 and was submitted to DHEC's laboratory for testing on 1 Aug 2016.

DHEC said several other puppies were for sale.

DHEC recommends that anyone who obtained or was exposed to a puppy there around this time should watch the animal for signs and symptoms of rabies and immediately seek veterinary care if the animal becomes ill. DHEC said signs and symptoms can include lethargy, fever, vomiting, weakness, not wanting to eat, aggression, abnormal behavior, difficulty walking, difficulty breathing, and difficulty swallowing.

If you have a question or concern about possible exposure, please contact DHEC's Environmental Health Services Spartanburg office at (864) 596-3327.

