******
[5] Rabies - South Carolina
Date: 5 Aug 2016
Source: WSPA [edited]
http://wspa.com/2016/08/05/five-exposed-to-rabid-puppy-in-chesnee/


According to DHEC, 5 people have been potentially exposed to rabies by a puppy that tested positive near Chesnee.

The dog, a German Shepherd mix puppy, was bought from a person outside the Burr's Trading Post on Old Stage Road in Chesnee in June 2016. The person was also selling other puppies. DHEC is recommending anyone who obtained or was exposed to a puppy there to watch the animal for signs and symptoms of rabies and immediately seek veterinary care if the dog becomes ill.

If you believe you bought any of these puppies and it died or you don't have it anymore, please contact your health care provider about possible exposure to rabies.

